A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Procurement – Purchase of Opioid Overdose Reversal Drugs From Opioid
3 Settlement Parties – Prohibition
4 FOR the purpose of prohibiting, under certain circumstances, the use of State funds to
5 purchase opioid overdose reversal drugs from certain entities; prohibiting certain
6 State contracts from being renewed on or after a certain date; and generally relating
7 to the use of State funds to purchase opioid overdose reversal drugs.
8 BY adding to
9 Article – State Finance and Procurement
10 Section 14–419
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
13 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
14 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
15 Article – State Finance and Procurement
16 14–419.
17 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “OPIOID OVERDOSE REVERSAL DRUG” HAS THE
18 MEANING STATED IN § 13–3501 OF THE HEALTH – GENERAL ARTICLE.
19 (B) (1) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION,
20 BEGINNING JULY 1, 2025, STATE FUNDS MAY NOT BE USED TO PURCHASE OPIOID
21 OVERDOSE REVERSAL DRUGS FROM A PERSON THAT WAS PARTY TO A SETTLEMENT
22 WITH ANY STATE DUE TO ITS ROLE IN THE MANUFACTURE, SALE, OR DISTRIBUTION
23 OF PRESCRIPTION OPIOIDS.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
