2 HOUSE BILL 395
1 (2) THE PROHIBITION UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION
2 DOES NOT APPLY TO:
3 (I) A PERSON THAT AGREED UNDER THE TERMS OF A
4 SETTLEMENT WITH ANY STATE, EXECUTED ON OR BEFORE SEPTEMBER 1, 2024, TO
5 PROVIDE OPIOID OVERDOSE REVERSAL DRUGS AS PART OF THE SETTLEMENT UNTIL
6 THE TERMS OF A SETTLEMENT WITH ANY STATE ARE FULFILLED; OR
7 (II) A PERSON WITH A STATE CONTRACT TO PROVIDE OPIOID
8 OVERDOSE REVERSAL DRUGS TO THE STATE EXECUTED ON OR BEFORE JUNE 30,
9 2025, UNTIL THE FULFILLMENT OF THE TERMS OF THE STATE CONTRACT.
10 (C) A STATE CONTRACT DESCRIBED UNDER SUBSECTION (B)(2)(II) OF THIS
11 SECTION MAY NOT BE RENEWED ON OR AFTER JULY 1, 2025.
12 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That a presently existing obligation
13 or contract right may not be impaired in any way by this Act.
14 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
15 1, 2025.

